<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Roene</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-19 17:28:38</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>My question is this: What level would be the miniumum required to get this weapon?  Keep in mind, a lower lvl character could pay off higher lvl characters to do some of the dirty work - e.g., paying 30pp for the death of (NPC) and looting rights.  Expensive, yes, a bit of leg-work yes, but cheaper than 800pp - any reason this is not attainable for a 16th lvl Pally?</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Roene</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-26 10:53:49</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>     Well, to answer my own post, I got this last night, although I feel luck had more to do with it than anything else.  After I got to the first island out of Freeport, it took me a while to figure out which Sister of E. makes Sentry Xyrin spawn.  After a little hunting about, I figured out it was the great warrior/leader, who is in one of the huts right off the docks (her name starts with: Sy).   I got Xyrin to spawn at the undead island, and then paddled my lvl 16 arse over there as fast as I could.  Fortunately for me, there were several high level Spectre hunters already keeping the MOB population low, so I didn't have to worry so much about being killed by a wandering Gargoyle.  They told me that she ran up to the Spectre spawn point in a suicide attempt before I even got to the island, which was odd.   They killed the offending spectre and saved her for me - for which I was eternally grateful.  So I gave her the potion of Marr, and she promptly disappeared, telling me she was too tired or busy to fight at the moment.   Hopes dashed that I'd have to go all the way back to Freeport to start over, I paddled back to the island of the Sisterhood.   I decided to talk to the Sisterhood leader again, and much to my surprise, Xyrin immediately spawned once again.  Figuring I may as well go give it another try, despite the fact I only had an empty container instead of the last sip of the potion of Marr, I paddled back over to the undead Island and gave Xyrin the empty potion bottle.  "Thank you for your donation to the Temple Marr," she said.  Ah, well, there goes that idea.   Just as I was giving up hope for the second time, I was befriended by a lvl 50 druid, which is always a good sign.  While we were talking, Xyrin suddenly sprang up, and bolted to the Spectre spawning ground, intent on dying a mangled death.  My new and powerful friend cleverly distracted the Spectre, luring it away from the others, and killed it down by the beach.  And that's were myself, my lvl 50 friend Jemene (who I owe my first virtual born child to) and Sentry Xyrin stood for about 10 more minutes.  Then, while Jemene and I were chatting, the most amazing thing happened; even though I somehow totally screwed up the quest, twice, Xyrin disappeared, leaving behind the Deepwater Harpoon!  This being the case, I have questions whether the whole Potion of Marr prelude is even necessary, although it is easy enough to do, and not too terribly time consuming if you have a list of the sentries and their location (which I got at Allakazam's EQ site).   <BR>
     So, to summarize the answer to my earlier question, YES, a level 16 pally CAN get this item, if they befriend a level 50 druid with a dislike for spectres.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
